Title: Can someone explain why AstraZeneca (AZN) hasn't tanked
Selftext: The side effect caused by the vaccine has proven to be true, 33 more cases found of blood clots in the brain due to 'heparin' like side effects and seems like it may be scratching the surface. Doubtful most countries will continue a roll-out with it. This all seems horrible and yet the stock price is barely dented.. what am I missing?
